message.content:
Rule Learning, Theory. 

The paper presents the clausal discovery engine claudien, which is a representative of the inductive logic programming paradigm and discovers regularities in data by means of first order clausal theories. This falls under the category of Rule Learning. The paper also discusses the declarative specification of the language bias, which determines the set of syntactically well-formed regularities, which is a theoretical aspect of the technique. Therefore, the paper also falls under the category of Theory.
